title: PPPP’s Imdad Ali Pitafi wins PS-59 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Imdad Ali Pitafi has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-59 Tando Allahyar-II by securing 62,771 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Muhammad Mohsin of Grand Democratic Alliance (GDA) who bagged 29,325 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 47.34%.
